headline: Starbucks gets a new dress code, Tesla falls behind, and Trump wants Powell out: Business news roundup
summary: Data released this week from the International Trade Association shows that arrivals of non-citizens to the United States by plane have declined by over 11% since March 2024.

headline: If You'd Invested $5,000 in Starbucks Stock 5 Years Ago, Here's How Much You'd Have Today
summary: Starbucks (NASDAQ: SBUX) hired a new CEO, Brian Niccol, who started last September.  Just before Niccol took over, Starbucks' same-store sales (comps) for the fiscal fourth-quarter of 2024 (that ended on Sep. 29, 2024) had dropped 7%.  To fully appreciate where Starbucks stands, it's instructive to look at the stock's historical performance.
